text: Iñaki Villanueva Martínez (born 10 February 1991) is a Spanish rugby sevens player. He competed for at the 2016 Summer Olympics in Brazil. He was part of the squad that won the 2016 Men's Rugby Sevens Final Olympic Qualification Tournament in Monaco and he played the Olympic tournament. His brother is Alejandro Villanueva, an American football offensive tackle for the Pittsburgh Steelers of the National Football League (NFL). == References == == External links == * Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:Andalusian sportspeople Category:Rugby sevens players at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic rugby sevens players of Spain Category:Spain international rugby sevens players Category:Spanish people of Basque descent Category:Spanish rugby union players
